    <div class="contentPane">
        <section class="l-page-block l-text-block">
            <div class="l-content-container container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col">
                        <h1>
More about the INTO London World Education Centre Centre                        </h1>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col">
                        <p>With a team of knowledgeable teachers, brilliant learning resources and technology-rich study areas, the INTO London World Education Centre is the perfect place to start your study abroad journey.</p>
<p>With modern e-learning tools, a library with excellent facilities and round-the-clock support, the Centre has everything you need to prepare for university study.</p>
<p><strong>Regulated by the Office for Students (OfS)</strong>
INTO London World Education Centre is regulated by the Office for Students (OfS). The OfS aims to help students succeed in Higher Education by ensuring they receive excellent information and guidance and get a high quality education that prepares them for the future, while protecting their interests. For more information, visit <a href="https://www.officeforstudents.org.uk/">Office for Students</a>.</p>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="l-detailed-info l-page-block block-bottom-spacer">
            <div class="l-content-container">
                <section>
                    

    <div class="l-accordian-container">
        <a class="accordian-control">
            Learning facilities
            <span>
                <em></em>
            </span>
        </a>

        <div class="l-accordian">
            <div>
                <p>Whatever your learning style, you’ll enjoy studying at the INTO London Study Centre. You’ll have access to a range of excellent facilities, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>29 classrooms, 3 lecture theatres and 9 private study rooms</li>
<li>a modern and bright art and design studio to inspire creative students</li>
<li>Moodle, the virtual learning environment that helps you revise and work outside the classroom</li>
<li>the Learning Resource Centre</li>
</ul>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="l-accordian-container">
            <a class="accordian-control">
                Is there a resource library at INTO London?
                <span>
                    <em></em>
                </span>
            </a>
            <div class="l-accordian">
                <div>
                    <p>The Learning Resource Centre is situated on the first floor of the INTO London World Education Centre. This study space is where you'll find materials to aid your studies including textbooks, DVDs, journals, CDs, newspapers, and printing and scanning facilities.</p>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="l-accordian-container">
            <a class="accordian-control">
                Does the Centre have a studio for Art and Design students?
                <span>
                    <em></em>
                </span>
            </a>
            <div class="l-accordian">
                <div>
                    <p>For students studying the Art and Design pathway, our light and bright Art and Design studio is an inspiring space equipped with everything you need to express your creativity.</p>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="l-accordian-container">
            <a class="accordian-control">
                Where can I eat at the Study Centre?
                <span>
                    <em></em>
                </span>
            </a>
            <div class="l-accordian">
                <div>
                    <p>When you're hungry, there's a café on the third floor of the building serving a selection of sandwiches, drinks and snacks – the perfect place to relax with your new friends over breakfast or lunch.</p>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

                    

